<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Everton have confirmed the signing of Abdoulaye Doucouré from relegated Watford. </p>

<p>The French midfielder has joined the Toffees in a deal believed to be worth around £22million after four season with the Hornets. He has signed a three-year deal, with an option for a fourth.</p>

<p>Doucoure's arrival at Goodison Park has topped off a busy couple days at the club, after they confirmed the signing of James Rodriguez from Real Madrid on Monday.</p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

